Preheat your #grill{} to high. Remove the stalk top from the @aubergine{1}, halve it lengthways, cut into 2cm wide strips, then chop into 2cm cubes. Place it on a #baking tray{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle on the @ground cumin{2%tsp} and drizzle over some @oil{some}. Mix well, then arrange in a single layer. Grill until browned, ~{10-12%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking to make sure the aubergine doesn't burn. Keep to one side when cooked.

Meanwhile, heat a glug of @oil{some} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Pan-fry the @gnocchi{300%g} until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to make sure they brown evenly.

In the meantime, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @basil{12%leaves} from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

When the gnocchi are ready, transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and return the now empty pan to medium heat. Add a splash of @oil{some} if your pan is dry and cook the shallot until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @tomato passata{1.5%cups} and @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}. Simmer for ~{5%minutes}, then stir in the basil and @baby spinach{125%g} until wilted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

When the aubergine has browned, add it to the tomato sauce, then spoon this on top of the gnocchi in the dish and stir together. In a #small bowl{}, mix the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, a drizzle of @oil{some} and a good grind of @black pepper{some}. Sprinkle this on top of the dish and grill until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on it, you don't want the crumb to burn!

Whilst the gratin is under the grill, toss the @wild rocket{40%g} in a #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{some}. Serve the gnocchi gratin in deep #bowls{} and finish with the rocket salad. Enjoy!